{
  "texts": [
    "Sam is a cognitive neuroscientist with a keen interest in covert attention (see Hooge et al., n.d., for an operationalization).",
    "While he has previously studied covert attention indirectly through response time measurements, he is now seeking a method to directly capture the direction in which covert attention is focused.",
    "He has read that one way to operationalize the direction of covert attention is by estimating the direction of microsaccades (Engbert & Kliegl, 2003).",
    "Microsaccades have been described as small (3-30 min arc) saccades that occur during instructed fixation (Poletti & Rucci, 2016; Nyström, Hansen, Andersson, & Hooge, 2016).",
    "The main requirement for Sam is an eye tracker that allows him to estimate when microsaccades occur and in what direction they go."
  ]
}